mplServiceTable.name: mplServiceTable
mplServiceTable.description: This table contains information on MP Links. These entries applies to LAN entries as well as WAN entries.

mplServiceEntry.name: mplServiceEntry
mplServiceEntry.description: Information on a particular MP Link.

mplServiceNumber.name: mplServiceNumber
mplServiceNumber.description: The MP Link number. The MP Link number is the same as the ifIndex for the corresponding upper group in the MIB-2 ifGroup.

mplServiceSlotNumber.name: mplServiceSlotNumber
mplServiceSlotNumber.description: The Slot position of the card. Set to 0 for stand-alone products.

mplServicePlugNumber.name: mplServicePlugNumber
mplServicePlugNumber.description: The plug number of the physical interface to which the MP Link is associated.

mplServicePlugName.name: mplServicePlugName
mplServicePlugName.description: The name of the physical interface to which the MP Link is associated.

mplServiceAttachment.name: mplServiceAttachment
mplServiceAttachment.description: The connector type used to connect the router to the LAN or WAN.

mplServiceProvider.name: mplServiceProvider
mplServiceProvider.description: The type of provider for this MP Link. For WAN links this specifies the actual protocol stack.

mplServiceBytesSentUpper.name: mplServiceBytesSentUpper
mplServiceBytesSentUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of octets (bytes) sent via the MP Link.

mplServiceBytesSentLower.name: mplServiceBytesSentLower
mplServiceBytesSentLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of octets (bytes) sent via the MP Link.

mplServiceBytesReceivedUpper.name: mplServiceBytesReceivedUpper
mplServiceBytesReceivedUpper.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of octets (bytes) sent via the MP Link.

mplServiceBytesReceivedLower.name: mplServiceBytesReceivedLower
mplServiceBytesReceivedLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of octets (bytes) received via the MP Link.

mplServiceLock.name: mplServiceLock
mplServiceLock.description: Indicates whether an MP Link has been locked from local management. The link may be unlocked by setting the value to 'off' and locked by setting the value to 'on'.

mplLanTable.name: mplLanTable
mplLanTable.description: This table contains information on LAN MP Links.

mplLanEntry.name: mplLanEntry
mplLanEntry.description: Information on a particular LAN MP Link.

mplLanNumber.name: mplLanNumber
mplLanNumber.description: The LAN MP Link number. The MP Link number is the same as the ifIndex for the corresponding upper group in the MIB-2 ifGroup.

mplLanRxCRCErrors.name: mplLanRxCRCErrors
mplLanRxCRCErrors.description: The number of frames received which were discarded due to Cyclic Redundancy Check (CRC) errors.

mplLanRxOverrun.name: mplLanRxOverrun
mplLanRxOverrun.description: The number of frames received which were lost due to RAM overloads within the router. This should not occur.

mplLanRxLong.name: mplLanRxLong
mplLanRxLong.description: The number of frames received which were discarded due to being larger than the maximum allowable length on the LAN.

mplLanRxOverflow.name: mplLanRxOverflow
mplLanRxOverflow.description: The number of frames received which were discarded due to lack of buffer capacity.

mplLanRxAlnErrors.name: mplLanRxAlnErrors
mplLanRxAlnErrors.description: The number of frames received which were discarded due to having the wrong frame length.

mplLanRxOuts.name: mplLanRxOuts
mplLanRxOuts.description: The number of frames received which were processed by higher layer protocols.

mplLanRxShort.name: mplLanRxShort
mplLanRxShort.description: The number of frames received which were discarded due to being shorter than the smallest allowable length on the LAN.

mplLanTxDeferred.name: mplLanTxDeferred
mplLanTxDeferred.description: The number of outgoing frames which were discarded due to a busy link.

mplLanTxUnderrun.name: mplLanTxUnderrun
mplLanTxUnderrun.description: The number of outgoing frames which were discarded due to overload.

mplLanTxSQEFailure.name: mplLanTxSQEFailure
mplLanTxSQEFailure.description: The number of outbound frames which had Signal Quality Errors (SQE).

mplLanTxExcDeferral.name: mplLanTxExcDeferral
mplLanTxExcDeferral.description: The number of transmission attempts which were delayed for more than 3.2 ms.

mplLanTxCollExceed.name: mplLanTxCollExceed
mplLanTxCollExceed.description: The number of outbound frames which were discarded due to exceeding 16 collisions on the Ethernet.

mplLanTxLateColl.name: mplLanTxLateColl
mplLanTxLateColl.description: The number of collisions occurring after the first 512 bytes of a frame had been transmitted.

mplLanTxCollisions.name: mplLanTxCollisions
mplLanTxCollisions.description: The number of outgoing frames which were discarded due to collisions that occurred during transmissions.

mplLanTxNoCarrier.name: mplLanTxNoCarrier
mplLanTxNoCarrier.description: The number of No Carrier detections during transmissions.

mplWanTable.name: mplWanTable
mplWanTable.description: This table contains information on WAN MP Links.

mplWanEntry.name: mplWanEntry
mplWanEntry.description: Information on a particular WAN MP Link.

mplWanNumber.name: mplWanNumber
mplWanNumber.description: The WAN MP Link number. The MP Link number is the same as the ifIndex for the corresponding upper group in the MIB-2 ifGroup.

mplWanDataState.name: mplWanDataState
mplWanDataState.description: The state of the MP Link seen from the higher layer protocol.

mplWanDataStateTimer.name: mplWanDataStateTimer
mplWanDataStateTimer.description: The time in seconds since the MP Link entered the Data State.

mplWanConnectState.name: mplWanConnectState
mplWanConnectState.description: Indicates the connection state of the WAN MP Link.

mplWanConnectStateTimer.name: mplWanConnectStateTimer
mplWanConnectStateTimer.description: The time in seconds since the MP Link entered the Connect State.

mplWanCompression.name: mplWanCompression
mplWanCompression.description: Indicates if data compression is used over the WAN MP Link. For frame relay links compression is not negotiated. For all other WAN protocols the compression will remain 'off' if not configured in both routers over the link.

mplWanCompressionType.name: mplWanCompressionType
mplWanCompressionType.description: Proprietary compression is used for LAPB and X.25 MP Links. For all other WAN protocols the Stac compression algorithm is used.

mplWanCallsSucceeded.name: mplWanCallsSucceeded
mplWanCallsSucceeded.description: The number of outgoing call which succeeded in making the connection.

mplWanCallsFailed.name: mplWanCallsFailed
mplWanCallsFailed.description: The number of outgoing call which failed to make the connection.

mplWanCallsAccepted.name: mplWanCallsAccepted
mplWanCallsAccepted.description: The number of incoming calls which were accepted on this link.

mplWanCallsRejected.name: mplWanCallsRejected
mplWanCallsRejected.description: The number of incoming calls which were rejected on this link.

mplWanRetries.name: mplWanRetries
mplWanRetries.description: The number of retries made for outgoing calls. May be set to zero which causes the call sequence to restarted.

mplWanDirection.name: mplWanDirection
mplWanDirection.description: Shows who initiated the call. 'incoming' if the call was initiated by the remote router and 'outgoing' if the call was inititated by this router. For PPP Multi Links the direction refers the the direction of the first slave link.

mplWanHasBackup.name: mplWanHasBackup
mplWanHasBackup.description: Indicates whether this link has a backup link configured for it.

mplWanBackupFor.name: mplWanBackupFor
mplWanBackupFor.description: Shows the primary link for which this link is the backup. The value 0 indicates that this is not a backup link.

mplWanBackupForAttachment.name: mplWanBackupForAttachment
mplWanBackupForAttachment.description: Indicates whether this link is a backup for an attachment.

mplWanFlags.name: mplWanFlags
mplWanFlags.description: WAN Flags dataCompressionMask 0x0001 acceptIncomingMask 0x0002 permitOutgoingMask 0x0004 permitTimeCutMask 0x0008 chapMask 0x0010 - CHAP, PPP only papMask 0x0020 - PAP, PPP only onlyReplyChapMask 0x0040 slaveLink 0x0080 blockOutgoing 0x0100 blockIncoming 0x0200 isLeased 0x0400 dataCompressionMode 0x0800 - PPP new-stac compression flag activitySoft 0x1000 - Activity timer only sends trap

mplWanPppMaster.name: mplWanPppMaster
mplWanPppMaster.description: Indicates the master link for a slave link. For master links and links not associated with a PPP Multi Link the value is 0.

mplWanPppSlaveUpCount.name: mplWanPppSlaveUpCount
mplWanPppSlaveUpCount.description: The number of slave links in Connect State 'up'. For slave links and links not associated with a PPP Multi Link the value is 1.

mplWanActivityTimeLeft.name: mplWanActivityTimeLeft
mplWanActivityTimeLeft.description: The time remaining in seconds until the Daily Activity Limit will close and lock the link. When the Daily Activity Limit has been reached, the link can be activated by setting mplWanActivity to 'on'.

mplWanActivity.name: mplWanActivity
mplWanActivity.description: Indicates whether the Daily Activity Limit has been reached and locked the link. To unlock the link set the value to 'off'. It is not possible to set to the value to 'on'.

mplWanTimer.name: mplWanTimer
mplWanTimer.description: Indicates whether an MP Link timer has locked the link. 'on' means the link is locked.

mplWanTimeTillTimecut.name: mplWanTimeTillTimecut
mplWanTimeTillTimecut.description: Time left in seconds until time cut

mplWanLastPacket.name: mplWanLastPacket
mplWanLastPacket.description: The first byte in this string identifies the type of packet that opened the link the last time. IP 1 Internet Protocols 0xcc IPX 2 Novell IPX 0x800000008137 STA_ETH 3 Bridge-Ether 0x800080c20007 STA_FRAG 4 Bridge-Frag 0x800080c2000d STA_BPDU 5 Bridge-BPDU 0x800080c2000e STA_CRAY 6 Bridge-Cray 0x800000800500 STA_ETH_FCS 15 Bridge-FCS After this byte follows a part of the packet header.

mplWanInTimeActive.name: mplWanInTimeActive
mplWanInTimeActive.description: The time in seconds that the link was in the Up state for incoming calls.

mplWanOutTimeActive.name: mplWanOutTimeActive
mplWanOutTimeActive.description: The time in seconds that the link was in the Up state for outcoming calls.

mplCompTable.name: mplCompTable
mplCompTable.description: Compression table with counters and other information regarding the Transmit and Receive Decoder.

mplCompNumber.name: mplCompNumber
mplCompNumber.description: The WAN MP Link number. The MP Link number is the same as the ifIndex for the corresponding upper group in the MIB-2 ifGroup.

mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalUpper.name: mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalUpper
mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes received by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalLower.name: mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalLower
mplCompRxDecRxBytesTotalLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes received by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompUpper.name: mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompUpper
mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes sent by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompLower.name: mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompLower
mplCompRxDecRxBytesDecompLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes sent by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecDecompressedUpper.name: mplCompRxDecDecompressedUpper
mplCompRxDecDecompressedUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of packets decompressed by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecDecompressedLower.name: mplCompRxDecDecompressedLower
mplCompRxDecDecompressedLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of packets decompressed by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsUpper.name: mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsUpper
mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of allocation errors in the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsLower.name: mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsLower
mplCompRxDecAllocErrorsLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of allocation errors in the Receive Decoder.

mplCompRxDecRemoteInits.name: mplCompRxDecRemoteInits
mplCompRxDecRemoteInits.description: Number of remote initializations by the Receive Decoder.

mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalUpper.name: mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalUpper
mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes received by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalLower.name: mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalLower
mplCompTxEncInBytesTotalLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes received by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompUpper.name: mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompUpper
mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes sent by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompLower.name: mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompLower
mplCompTxEncTxBytesCompLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of bytes sent by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncCompressedUpper.name: mplCompTxEncCompressedUpper
mplCompTxEncCompressedUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of packets compressed by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncCompressedLower.name: mplCompTxEncCompressedLower
mplCompTxEncCompressedLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of packets compressed by the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsUpper.name: mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsUpper
mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsUpper.description: The upper 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of allocation errors in the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsLower.name: mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsLower
mplCompTxEncAllocErrorsLower.description: The lower 32 bits of the 64 bits counter which is the number of allocation errors in the Transmit Decoder.

mplCompTxEncLocalInits.name: mplCompTxEncLocalInits
mplCompTxEncLocalInits.description: Number of local initializations by the Receive Decoder.

mplIfStackTable.name: mplIfStackTable
mplIfStackTable.description: This table contains information on the relationships between the multiple sub-layers of network interfaces. In particular, it contains information on which sub- layers run 'on top of' which other sub-layers. Each sub-layer corresponds to a conceptual row in the ifTable.

mplIfStackEntry.name: mplIfStackEntry
mplIfStackEntry.description: Information on a particular relationship between two sub-layers, specifying that one sub-layer runs on 'top' of the other sub-layer. Each sub-layer corresponds to a conceptual row in the ifTable.

mplIfStackNumber.name: mplIfStackNumber
mplIfStackNumber.description: The MP Link number. The MP Link number is the same as the ifIndex for the corresponding upper group in the MIB-2 ifGroup.

mplIfStackLowerLayer.name: mplIfStackLowerLayer
mplIfStackLowerLayer.description: The value of ifIndex corresponding to the lower sub- layer of the relationship, i.e., the sub-layer which runs 'below' the sub-layer identified by the corresponding instance of mplIfStackNumber. If there is no lower sub-layer, then this object has the value 0.

mplGeneralOverviewChange.name: mplGeneralOverviewChange
mplGeneralOverviewChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time any MP Link seen from the overview changed state or the like.

mplGeneralIfgroupStatus.name: mplGeneralIfgroupStatus
mplGeneralIfgroupStatus.description: A table describing the status of all ifgroups. Bit 0-3: State: 001 = Up, 010 = Down, 011 = Timecut, 100 = Disabled 111 = Lock. Bit 4: Reserved for future use Bit 5: IP status: 1 = Up, 0 = Down. (This bit is only used for MPLinks) Bit 6: IPX status: 1 = Up, 0 = Down. (This bit is only used for MPLinks) Bit 7: Bridge status: 1 = Up, 0 = Down. (This bit is only used for MPLinks)

mplLockEvent.name: mplLockEvent
mplLockEvent.description: Lock state changed to <mplServiceLock> for link <mplServiceNumber>. This trap is sent when an MP Link is locked or unlocked from local management or via SNMP.

mplWanRetriesEvent.name: mplWanRetriesEvent
mplWanRetriesEvent.description: Max. retries exceeded (<mplWanRetries>) for link <mplWanNumber>. This trap is sent when an MP Link has had more failed connect-attempts than allowed in the configuration.

mplWanActivityEvent.name: mplWanActivityEvent
mplWanActivityEvent.description: Daily Activity Limit has been reached. Link <mplWanNumber> locked. This trap is sent when the Daily Activity Limit has been reached and locked the link.

mplWanTimerEvent.name: mplWanTimerEvent
mplWanTimerEvent.description: Link timer has changed lock state to <WanTimer> for link <WanNumber>. This trap is sent when an MP Link timer has locked or unlocked the link.
